cube/cli/main.py` — invoke and status commands\n251: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` — Updated exports\n252: - [ ] `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` — get_agent_runtime method\n253: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_invoke_runtime.py` — InvokeRuntime unit tests\n254: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_status_runtime.py` — StatusRuntime unit tests\n255: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_cli_invoke.py` — CLI invoke tests\n256: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_cli_status.py` — CLI status tests\n257: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_invoke.py` — Invoke integration tests\n258: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_status.py` — Status integration tests\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## Verification Commands\n263: \n264: ```bash\n265: # Build/install verification\n266: pip install -e .\n267: \n268: # Import verification\n269: python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime\"\n270: python -c \"from agentcube.cli.main import invoke, status\"\n271: \n272: # CLI entry point verification\n273: kubectl-agentcube --help\n274: kubectl-agentcube invoke --help\n275: kubectl-agentcube status --help\n276: \n277: # Unit test verification\n278: pytest tests/unit/test_invoke_runtime.py -v\n279: pytest tests/unit/test_status_runtime.py -v\n280: pytest tests/unit/test_cli_invoke.py -v\n281: pytest tests/unit/test_cli_status.py -v\n282: \n283: # Integration tests\n284: pytest tests/integration/test_invoke.py -v\n285: pytest tests/integration/test_status.py -v\n286: \n287: # Coverage report\n288: pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n289: \n290: # Lint verification\n291: ruff check agentcube/\n292: mypy agentcube/\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## Definition of Done\n298: \n299: - [ ] All 101 tasks complete\n300: - [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e .`)\n301: - [ ] CLI commands work (`kubectl-agentcube invoke`, `kubectl-agentcube status`)\n302: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for each module)\n303: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n304: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n305: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n306: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Dependencies\n311: \n312: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework (already present)\n313: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already present)\n314: - `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing (already present)\n315: - `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress indicators and tables (already present)\n316: - `httpx>=0.24.0` — HTTP client for invocations (NEW)\n317: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0` — K8s client (already present)\n318: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n319: - `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting (already present)\n320: - `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities (already present)\n321: - `respx>=0.20.0` — httpx mocking for tests (NEW)\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Design Notes\n326: \n327: - **Provider selection:** `--provider` accepts \"agentcube\" (AgentRuntime CR) or \"k8s\" (Deployment/Service)\n328: - **Payload format:** JSON string passed to `--payload`, validated before sending\n329: - **Header format:** `\"Key: Value\"` format, parsed into dict\n330: - **Session header:** `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` automatically added if session_id in metadata\n331: - **Status exit codes:** Exit code 1 for \"not_published\" or \"error\" statuses\n332: - **URL construction for agentcube:** `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n333: - **Error handling:** All errors use `_handle_error()` for consistent display\n334: - **Progress indication:** Rich Progress spinner during invoke operation\n335: - **Output formatting:** JSON for invoke, Rich Table for status\n\n(End of file - total 335 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-023  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` and `status` CLI commands enable users to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends HTTP requests to agents with JSON payloads, while `status` retrieves the deployment state from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — InvokeRuntime Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775894138807,"end":1775894138823}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894138827,"sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8a0af2001O2vKuuU1kx3pUe","messageID":"msg_d7b89efed001SMFlVXlVc4h0g9","sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/notes.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/notes.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Notes\n2: \n3: ## Development Notes\n4: \n5: ### Design Decisions\n6: - Sync/async execution modes for flexibility\n7: - Configurable polling intervals for status command\n8: - Multiple input formats (JSON, file, key-value)\n9: \n10: ### Technical Considerations\n11: - Use shared HTTP client from existing CLI modules\n12: - Follow existing error handling patterns\n13: - Ensure proper exit codes for scripting support\n14: \n15: ### API Assumptions\n16: - Backend provides `/api/v1/executions` endpoints\n17: - Authentication handled via existing auth module\n18: - Execution states: pending, running, completed, failed, cancelled\n19: \n20: ## Change Log\n21: \n22: ### 2026-04-11\n23: - Initial scaffold creation\n24: - Created spec.yaml, delta-spec.md, design.md, plan.md, tasks.md, notes.md, tests.md\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Notes\n\n## Development Notes\n\n### Design Decisions\n- Sync/async execution modes for flexibility\n- Configurable polling intervals for status command\n- Multiple input formats (JSON, file, key-value)\n\n### Technical Considerations\n- Use shared HTTP client from existing CLI modules\n- Follow existing error handling patterns\n- Ensure proper exit codes for scripting support\n\n### API Assumptions\n- Backend provides `/api/v1/executions` endpoints\n- Authentication handled via existing auth module\n- Execution states: pending, running, completed, failed, cancelled\n\n## Change Log","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/notes.md","time":{"start":1775894138810,"end":1775894138825}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775894138853,"sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8a0fcb001NRyjODaOlbWnKg","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b89efed001SMFlVXlVc4h0g9","sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28699,"input":4,"output":215,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":7617,"read":20863}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775894145592,"sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8a2a330010z7dj3rctcl8zt","messageID":"msg_d7b8a1000001Ppx5Jg7L9RB4Nv","sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894148995,"sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8a2e04001BiJDXkx7DVc1pG","messageID":"msg_d7b8a1000001Ppx5Jg7L9RB4Nv","sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: CLI Invoke/Status Commands (AR-023)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-023  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Provide the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to agent endpoints, while the `status` command retrieves deployment status from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Invoke command - CLI options and defaults\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Default option values\n21: - **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke` without any options\n22: - **WHEN** the command parses arguments\n23: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n24:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n25:   - `payload` = `\"{}\"` (empty JSON object)\n26:   - `header_list` = `None`\n27:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n28:   - `verbose` = `False`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Workspace path override\n31: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `-f /path/to/agent` or `--workspace /path/to/agent`\n32: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided path\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Payload specification\n36: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload '{\"input\": \"test\"}'`\n37: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL parse the payload as JSON and include it in the HTTP POST request\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Multiple header options\n41: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\" --header \"X-Custom: value\"`\n42: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n43: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL include both headers in the HTTP request\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider selection - AgentCube\n46: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n47: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with AgentCube provider to invoke via AgentRuntime CR endpoint\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Provider selection - Kubernetes\n51: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n52: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n53: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with K8s provider for direct HTTP invocation to the NodePort Service\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: Invoke command - payload and header validation\n58: \n59: The system SHALL validate the payload and headers before sending the request.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Invalid JSON payload\n62: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload 'invalid json'`\n63: - **WHEN** the CLI attempts to parse the payload\n64: - **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message in red indicating invalid JSON\n65: - **AND** exit with code `1` before invoking the runtime\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid header format (missing colon)\n68: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"InvalidHeaderWithoutColon\"`\n69: - **WHEN** the CLI parses the header\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message indicating expected `key:value` format\n71: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Valid payload parsing\n74: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'`\n75: - **WHEN** the payload is parsed\n76: - **THEN** the system SHALL successfully convert it to a Python dictionary\n77: - **AND** pass it to `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Header parsing with colon in value\n80: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"Authorization: Bearer: token:with:colons\"`\n81: - **WHEN** the header is parsed\n82: - **THEN** the system SHALL split only on the first colon\n83: - **AND** produce header key `Authorization` with value `Bearer: token:with:colons`\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### Requirement: Invoke command - workspace metadata validation\n88: \n89: The system SHALL validate workspace metadata before attempting to invoke.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n92: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n93: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` is invoked\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Missing agent_metadata.yaml\n97: - **GIVEN** the workspace exists but contains no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` file\n98: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n99: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating the metadata file is missing\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Agent not published\n102: - **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but has no `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint`\n103: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n104: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the agent must be published first\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Requirement: Invoke command - HTTP invocation\n109: \n110: The system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the agent endpoint with appropriate headers.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Direct HTTP invocation to K8s NodePort\n113: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and metadata contains `k8s_deployment.service_url`\n114: - **AND** the payload is valid JSON\n115: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` is called\n116: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `{service_url}` with JSON body\n117: - **AND** include custom headers if provided\n118: - **AND** return the response JSON\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: AgentCube CR invocation via Router\n121: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and metadata contains `router_url` and `agent_id`\n122: - **AND** `k8s_deployment.type` is `\"AgentRuntime\"`\n123: - **WHEN** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` is called\n124: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n125: - **AND** include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` if `session_id` exists in metadata\n126: - **AND** include `Content-Type: application/json` header\n127: - **AND** return the response\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Session header from metadata\n130: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id = \"abc-123\"`\n131: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n132: - **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc-123`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: Successful invocation response\n135: - **GIVEN** the HTTP request succeeds with status 200\n136: - **AND** the response contains valid JSON `{\"result\": \"success\"}`\n137: - **WHEN** the response is received\n138: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display the response in a formatted manner\n139: - **AND** exit with code `0`\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: HTTP error response\n142: - **GIVEN** the HTTP request returns status 4xx or 5xx\n143: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n144: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception\n145: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print the error and exit with code `1`\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: Invoke command - error handling\n150: \n151: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully using the `_handle_error` pattern.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Error with verbose mode\n154: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during invoke and `--verbose` is enabled\n155: - **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n156: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n157:   1. Print \"Error invoking agent: {error message}\" in red\n158:   2. Print the full traceback\n159:   3. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Error without verbose mode\n162: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during invoke and `--verbose` is disabled\n163: - **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n164: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n165:   1. Print \"Error invoking agent: {error message}\" in red\n166:   2. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)` without printing traceback\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Network timeout\n169: - **GIVEN** the agent endpoint is unreachable or times out\n170: - **WHEN** the HTTP request is made\n171: - **THEN** the system SHALL catch the timeout/connection error\n172: - **AND** raise a user-friendly error message\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ### Requirement: Status command - CLI options and defaults\n177: \n178: The system SHALL provide a `status` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Default option values\n181: - **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube status` without any options\n182: - **WHEN** the command parses arguments\n183: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n184:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n185:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n186:   - `verbose` = `False`\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Workspace path override\n189: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `-f /path/to/agent` or `--workspace /path/to/agent`\n190: - **WHEN** the status command executes\n191: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided path\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Provider selection - AgentCube\n194: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n195: - **WHEN** the status command executes\n196: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with AgentCube provider to check AgentRuntime CR status\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Provider selection - Kubernetes\n199: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n200: - **WHEN** the status command executes\n201: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with K8s provider to check Deployment status\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ### Requirement: Status command - workspace metadata validation\n206: \n207: The system SHALL validate workspace metadata before attempting to check status.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n210: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n211: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` is invoked\n212: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Missing agent_metadata.yaml\n215: - **GIVEN** the workspace exists but contains no metadata file\n216: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n217: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating the metadata file is missing\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Agent not published\n220: - **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but has no `agent_id`\n221: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` runs\n222: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_published\", \"message\": \"Agent has not been published\"}`\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ### Requirement: Status command - status retrieval\n227: \n228: The system SHALL retrieve and display agent status from the appropriate provider.\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: K8s provider - Deployment status\n231: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and Kubernetes client initializes successfully\n232: - **AND** metadata contains `k8s_deployment.name` and `k8s_deployment.namespace`\n233: - **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` is invoked\n234: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)`\n235: - **AND** return status including:\n236:   - `status`: `\"running\"`, `\"pending\"`, `\"failed\"`, or `\"not_found\"`\n237:   - `deployment_name`: name of the Deployment\n238:   - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n239:   - `replicas`: number of desired replicas\n240:   - `ready_replicas`: number of ready replicas\n241:   - `service_url`: the NodePort service URL if available\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider - CR status\n244: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and the CR exists in Kubernetes\n245: - **AND** metadata contains `agent_id` and `k8s_deployment.name`\n246: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` is invoked\n247: - **THEN** the system SHALL query the AgentRuntime CR\n248: - **AND** read status from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present\n249: - **AND** return `status`, `agentEndpoint`, and other CR status fields\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: AgentCube CR - status present\n252: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists with `.status.status = \"Ready\"`\n253: - **AND** `.status.agentEndpoint = \"http://router/v1/...\"`\n254: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` processes the CR\n255: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"Ready\", \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://router/v1/...\", ...}`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: AgentCube CR - no status field\n258: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no `.status` field\n259: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` processes the CR\n260: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\", \"message\": \"CR exists but status not yet populated\"}`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: AgentCube CR - not found\n263: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR does not exist in the namespace\n264: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` attempts to get the CR\n265: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"message\": \"AgentRuntime CR not found\"}`\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ### Requirement: Status command - output formatting\n270: \n271: The system SHALL display status information in a Rich `Table` format.\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Successful status display\n274: - **GIVEN** the status is successfully retrieved\n275: - **WHEN** the CLI displays the result\n276: - **THEN** the system SHALL render a Rich `Table` with:\n277:   - Property column (e.g., \"Status\", \"Agent ID\", \"Endpoint\", \"Replicas\")\n278:   - Value column with appropriate styling\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Running status styling\n281: - **GIVEN** the agent status is `\"running\"` or `\"Ready\"`\n282: - **WHEN** displayed in the table\n283: - **THEN** the status value SHALL be styled in green\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Pending status styling\n286: - **GIVEN** the agent status is `\"pending\"` or `\"created_no_status\"`\n287: - **WHEN** displayed in the table\n288: - **THEN** the status value SHALL be styled in yellow\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Failed/error status styling\n291: - **GIVEN** the agent status is `\"failed\"`, `\"error\"`, or `\"not_found\"`\n292: - **WHEN** displayed in the table\n293: - **THEN** the status value SHALL be styled in red\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ### Requirement: Status command - exit codes\n298: \n299: The system SHALL exit with appropriate codes based on status.\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Status is not_published\n302: - **GIVEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n303: - **WHEN** the CLI processes the result\n304: - **THEN** the system SHALL print guidance to publish first\n305: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Status is error or not_found\n308: - **GIVEN** `get_status` returns `status` in `[\"error\", \"failed\", \"not_found\", \"not_found_in_k8s\"]`\n309: - **WHEN** the CLI processes the result\n310: - **THEN** the system SHALL exit with code `1`\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Status is running or ready\n313: - **GIVEN** `get_status` returns `status` in `[\"running\", \"Ready\", \"ready\"]`\n314: - **WHEN** the CLI processes the result\n315: - **THEN** the system SHALL exit with code `0`\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: Status command - error handling\n320: \n321: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully using the `_handle_error` pattern.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Error with verbose mode\n324: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during status check and `--verbose` is enabled\n325: - **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n326: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n327:   1. Print \"Error checking agent status: {error message}\" in red\n328:   2. Print the full traceback\n329:   3. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Error without verbose mode\n332: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during status check and `--verbose` is disabled\n333: - **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n334: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n335:   1. Print \"Error checking agent status: {error message}\" in red\n336:   2. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)` without printing traceback\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Kubernetes client initialization failure\n339: - **GIVEN** the Kubernetes client fails to initialize (e.g., no kubeconfig, invalid credentials)\n340: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated in `StatusRuntime`\n341: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception that is propagated through `_handle_error`\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## File Index\n346: \n347: | Path | Purpose |\n348: |------|---------|\n349: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke` and `status` command definitions |\n350: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` class with invocation logic |\n351: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` class with status retrieval logic |\n352: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for K8s status queries |\n353: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for CR status queries |\n354: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for loading agent metadata |\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ## Dependencies\n359: \n360: | Dependency | Purpose |\n361: |------------|---------|\n362: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n363: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation for metadata |\n364: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML parsing for metadata files |\n365: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for agent invocation |\n366: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes client for CR queries (optional) |\n367: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich text output and table formatting |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## CLI Usage Examples\n372: \n373: ```bash\n374: # Invoke agent with default empty payload\n375: agentcube invoke -f ./my-agent\n376: \n377: # Invoke agent with custom payload\n378: agentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --payload '{\"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\"}'\n379: \n380: # Invoke agent with custom headers\n381: agentcube invoke -f ./my-agent \\\n382:   --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}' \\\n383:   --header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\" \\\n384:   --header \"X-Request-ID: abc-123\"\n385: \n386: # Invoke agent on Kubernetes provider\n387: agentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --provider k8s --payload '{\"data\": [1,2,3]}'\n388: \n389: # Check agent status\n390: agentcube status -f ./my-agent\n391: \n392: # Check status for Kubernetes deployment\n393: agentcube status -f ./my-agent --provider k8s\n394: \n395: # Check status with verbose output\n396: agentcube status -f ./my-agent --verbose\n397: ```\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## Integration Points\n402: \n403: | Component | Integration |\n404: |-----------|-------------|\n405: | `PublishRuntime` | Reads metadata created during publish phase |\n406: | `KubernetesProvider` | Queries Deployment and Service status |\n407: | `AgentCubeProvider` | Queries AgentRuntime CR status |\n408: | `MetadataService` | Loads agent metadata for endpoint discovery |\n409: | `InvokeRuntime` | Makes HTTP requests to agent endpoints |\n410: | `StatusRuntime` | Aggregates status from various providers |\n411: \n412: ---\n413: \n414: ## Notes\n415: \n416: - The `invoke` command requires a published agent with valid `agent_endpoint` (for K8s) or `router_url` (for AgentCube)\n417: - For `provider=agentcube`, the metadata must include `router_url` to construct the invocation URL\n418: - For `provider=k8s`, the metadata must include `k8s_deployment.service_url` or derive it from `node_port`\n419: - The `status` command reads from `k8s_deployment` metadata populated by the `publish` command\n420: - Both commands use the `_handle_error` pattern consistent with other CLI commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`)\n\n(End of file - total 420 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: CLI Invoke/Status Commands (AR-023)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-023  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nProvide the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to agent endpoints, while the `status` command retrieves deployment status from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - CLI options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775894148982,"end":1775894148994}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894148999,"sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8a32d00013bkYVWSpalUwf9","messageID":"msg_d7b8a1000001Ppx5Jg7L9RB4Nv","sessionID":"ses_2847648f1ffemm5w2whyZmaXXZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document provides technical implementation details for the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands for the AgentCube project. These commands enable users to interact with deployed agents and check their deployment status.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-023  \n8: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n9: **Language:** Python  \n10: **Size:** M\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### Component Diagram\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                              CLI Layer                                        │\n21: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n22: │  │   invoke command    │    │   status command    │                         │\n23: │  │   (main.py:379)     │    │   (main.py:409)     │                         │\n24: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n25: │             │                          │                                     │\n26: │             ▼                          ▼                                     │\n27: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n28: │  │   InvokeRuntime     │    │   StatusRuntime     │                         │\n29: │  │   (invoke_runtime)  │    │   (status_runtime)  │                         │\n30: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n31: └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┘\n32:               │                          │\n33:               ▼                          ▼\n34: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n35: │                           Service Layer                                       │\n36: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐  │\n37: │  │  MetadataService    │    │ AgentCubeProvider   │    │KubernetesProvider│  │\n38: │  │  (load metadata)    │    │  (CR operations)    │    │ (K8s resources)  │  │\n39: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘    └────────┬────────┘  │\n40: └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────┘\n41:               │                          │                        │\n42:               ▼                          ▼                        ▼\n43: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44: │                           External APIs                                       │\n45: │       Agent Metadata YAML         AgentRuntime CR           K8s API         │\n46: │     (agent_metadata.yaml)    (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)  (Deployment)   │\n47: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Data Flow\n51: \n52: #### Invoke Command Flow\n53: ```\n54: 1. CLI parses arguments (workspace, payload, headers, provider)\n55: 2. Validate payload is valid JSON\n56: 3. Parse header strings into dict (format: \"key:value\")\n57: 4. InvokeRuntime.invoke():\n58:    a. Load metadata from workspace\n59:    b. Validate prerequisites (agent_id for agentcube, endpoint for k8s)\n60:    c. Determine endpoint URL based on provider\n61:    d. Add session header if session_id exists in metadata\n62:    e. Send HTTP POST with payload\n63:    f. Return response\n64: 5. CLI formats and displays result\n65: ```\n66: \n67: #### Status Command Flow\n68: ```\n69: 1. CLI parses arguments (workspace, provider)\n70: 2. StatusRuntime.get_status():\n71:    a. Load metadata from workspace\n72:    b. If no agent_id → return \"not_published\"\n73:    c. Based on provider:\n74:       - agentcube: Query AgentRuntime CR status\n75:       - k8s: Query Deployment/Service status\n76:    d. Return status dict\n77: 3. CLI displays status in Rich Table\n78: 4. Exit code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\"\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## Module Structure\n84: \n85: ### File Layout\n86: \n87: | Path | Role |\n88: |------|------|\n89: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke()` and `status()` commands (lines 379-430) |\n90: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` class for agent invocation |\n91: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` class for status checking |\n92: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for loading/saving metadata |\n93: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for CR operations |\n94: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for K8s resource operations |\n95: \n96: ### Dependencies\n97: \n98: ```\n99: invoke/status commands\n100:     ├── InvokeRuntime / StatusRuntime\n101:     │       ├── MetadataService\n102:     │       │       └── AgentMetadata (Pydantic model)\n103:     │       ├── AgentCubeProvider (if provider=agentcube)\n104:     │       │       └── Kubernetes client (custom resources)\n105:     │       └── KubernetesProvider (if provider=k8s)\n106:     │               └── Kubernetes client (Deployment/Service)\n107:     └── httpx (for HTTP requests in invoke)\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Implementation Details\n113: \n114: ### 1. CLI Commands (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n115: \n116: #### Invoke Command\n117: \n118: ```python\n119: @app.command()\n120: def invoke(\n121:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n122:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n123:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n124:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n125:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n126: ) -> None:\n127: ```\n128: \n129: **Implementation Logic:**\n130: \n131: ```python\n132: def invoke(...) -> None:\n133:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n134:     \n135:     # 1. Validate JSON payload\n136:     try:\n137:         payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n138:     except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n139:         console.print(f\"Error: Invalid JSON payload - {e}\", style=\"red\")\n140:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n141:     \n142:     # 2. Parse headers\n143:     headers = {}\n144:     if header_list:\n145:         for header in header_list:\n146:             if \":\" not in header:\n147:                 console.print(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\", style=\"red\")\n148:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n149:             key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n150:             headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n151:     \n152:     # 3. Create runtime and invoke\n153:     runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n154:     \n155:     try:\n156:         with Progress(...) as progress:\n157:             task = progress.add_task(\"Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n158:             result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)\n159:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n160:         \n161:         # 4. Display result\n162:         console.print(\"[green]✓[/green] Agent invoked successfully!\")\n163:         console.print_json(data=result)\n164:         \n165:     except Exception as e:\n166:         _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### Status Command\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: @app.command()\n173: def status(\n174:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n175:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n176:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n177: ) -> None:\n178: ```\n179: \n180: **Implementation Logic:**\n181: \n182: ```python\n183: def status(...) -> None:\n184:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n185:     \n186:     runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n187:     \n188:     try:\n189:         status_result = runtime.get_status(workspace_path)\n190:         \n191:         # Display in Rich Table\n192:         table = Table(title=\"Agent Status\")\n193:         table.add_column(\"Property\", style=\"cyan\")\n194:         table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n195:         \n196:         for key, value in status_result.items():\n197:             table.add_row(key, str(value))\n198:         \n199:         console.print(table)\n200:         \n201:         # Exit with code 1 if not published or error\n202:         if status_result.get(\"status\") in (\"not_published\", \"error\"):\n203:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n204:             \n205:     except Exception as e:\n206:         _handle_error(e, \"checking status\", verbose)\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ### 2. InvokeRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n212: \n213: #### Class Definition\n214: \n215: ```python\n216: class InvokeRuntime:\n217:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n218:     \n219:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n220:         self.verbose = verbose\n221:         self.provider = provider\n222:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n223:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n224:     \n225:     def invoke(\n226:         self,\n227:         workspace_path: Path,\n228:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n229:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n230:     ) -> Any:\n231:         \"\"\"Invoke the agent.\"\"\"\n232:         headers = headers or {}\n233:         \n234:         # Validate prerequisites and get metadata\n235:         metadata, endpoint, agent_id = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n236:         \n237:         # Add session header if available\n238:         if metadata.session_id:\n239:             headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n240:         \n241:         # Invoke based on provider\n242:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n243:             return self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path)\n244:         else:\n245:             return self._direct_http_invocation(endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path)\n246: ```\n247: \n248: #### Key Methods\n249: \n250: **`_validate_invoke_prerequisites`**\n251: ```python\n252: def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n253:     \"\"\"Validate that the agent can be invoked.\n254:     \n255:     Returns:\n256:         Tuple of (metadata, endpoint, agent_id)\n257:     \n258:     Raises:\n259:         ValueError: If metadata is missing required fields.\n260:     \"\"\"\n261:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n262:     \n263:     if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n264:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n265:             raise ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\")\n266:         if not metadata.router_url:\n267:             raise ValueError(\"router_url is required in metadata for agentcube provider\")\n268:         endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint or metadata.router_url\n269:         return metadata, endpoint, metadata.agent_id\n270:     else:\n271:         # k8s provider\n272:         if not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n273:             raise ValueError(\"No Kubernetes deployment found. Run 'publish --provider k8s' first.\")\n274:         endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint or self._build_k8s_endpoint(metadata)\n275:         return metadata, endpoint, metadata.agent_name\n276: ```\n277: \n278: **`_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`**\n279: ```python\n280: async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n281:     self,\n282:     agent_id: str,\n283:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n284:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n285:     endpoint: str,\n286:     workspace_path: Path,\n287: ) -> Any:\n288:     \"\"\"Invoke agent through AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR).\n289:     \n290:     For AgentRuntime CR deployments, rewrites URL to:\n291:     {base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n292:     \"\"\"\n293:     import httpx\n294:     \n295:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n296:     \n297:     # Build invocation URL\n298:     if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n299:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n300:         agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n301:         base_url = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n302:         invoke_url = f\"{base_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n303:     else:\n304:         invoke_url = endpoint\n305:     \n306:     # Make request\n307:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n308:         response = await client.post(\n309:             invoke_url,\n310:             json=payload,\n311:             headers=headers,\n312:             timeout=30.0,\n313:         )\n314:         response.raise_for_status()\n315:         return response.json()\n316: ```\n317: \n318: **`_direct_http_invocation`**\n319: ```python\n320: async def _direct_http_invocation(\n321:     self,\n322:     endpoint: str,\n323:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n324:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n325:     workspace_path: Path,\n326: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n327:     \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments.\"\"\"\n328:     import httpx\n329:     \n330:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n331:         response = await client.post(\n332:             endpoint,\n333:             json=payload,\n334:             headers=headers,\n335:             timeout=30.0,\n336:         )\n337:         response.raise_for_status()\n338:         return response.json()\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### 3. StatusRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n344: \n345: #### Class Definition\n346: \n347: ```python\n348: class StatusRuntime:\n349:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for checking agent status.\"\"\"\n350:     \n351:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n352:         self.verbose = verbose\n353:         self.provider = provider\n354:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n355:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n356:     \n357:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n358:         \"\"\"Get the agent status.\n359:         \n360:         Returns:\n361:             Dict with keys:\n362:             - status: \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\", \"not_published\", etc.\n363:             - agent_name: The agent name\n364:             - agent_id: The agent ID (if published)\n365:             - endpoint: The agent endpoint (if available)\n366:             - provider: The provider used\n367:             - message: Human-readable status message\n368:         \"\"\"\n369:         provider = provider or self.provider\n370:         \n371:         try:\n372:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n373:         except FileNotFoundError:\n374:             return {\n375:                 \"status\": \"error\",\n376:                 \"message\": f\"No metadata found in {workspace_path}\",\n377:             }\n378:         \n379:         # Check if published\n380:         if not metadata.agent_id and not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n381:             return {\n382:                 \"status\": \"not_published\",\n383:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n384:                 \"message\": \"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\",\n385:             }\n386:         \n387:         # Get status based on provider\n388:         if provider == \"agentcube\":\n389:             return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n390:         else:\n391:             return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n392: ```\n393: \n394: #### Key Methods\n395: \n396: **`_get_k8s_status`**\n397: ```python\n398: def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n399:     \"\"\"Get status for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n400:     from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n401:     \n402:     if not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n403:         return {\n404:             \"status\": \"error\",\n405:             \"message\": \"No Kubernetes deployment information found\",\n406:         }\n407:     \n408:     k8s = KubernetesProvider(\n409:         namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n410:         verbose=self.verbose,\n411:     )\n412:     \n413:     try:\n414:         agent_status = k8s.get_agent_status(metadata.k8s_deployment[\"name\"])\n415:         return {\n416:             \"status\": agent_status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n417:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n418:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n419:             \"endpoint\": metadata.agent_endpoint,\n420:             \"provider\": \"k8s\",\n421:             \"deployment\": metadata.k8s_deployment,\n422:             \"message\": f\"Deployment is {agent_status.get('status', 'unknown')}\",\n423:         }\n424:     except Exception as e:\n425:         return {\n426:             \"status\": \"error\",\n427:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n428:             \"message\": f\"Failed to get status: {e}\",\n429:         }\n430: ```\n431: \n432: **`_get_cr_k8s_status`**\n433: ```python\n434: def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n435:     \"\"\"Get status for AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n436:     from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n437:     \n438:     if not metadata.agent_id:\n439:         return {\n440:             \"status\": \"not_published\",\n441:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n442:             \"message\": \"Agent has not been published\",\n443:         }\n444:     \n445:     namespace = \"default\"\n446:     if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n447:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n448:     \n449:     provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n450:     \n451:     try:\n452:         cr = provider.get_agent_runtime(metadata.agent_name, namespace)\n453:         \n454:         if cr is None:\n455:             return {\n456:                 \"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\",\n457:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n458:                 \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n459:                 \"message\": \"AgentRuntime CR not found in Kubernetes\",\n460:             }\n461:         \n462:         # Extract status from CR\n463:         cr_status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n464:         if cr_status:\n465:             status = cr_status.get(\"status\", \"created_no_status\")\n466:             endpoint = cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\") or metadata.agent_endpoint\n467:         else:\n468:             status = \"created_no_status\"\n469:             endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint\n470:         \n471:         return {\n472:             \"status\": status,\n473:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n474:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n475:             \"endpoint\": endpoint,\n476:             \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n477:             \"message\": f\"AgentRuntime is {status}\",\n478:         }\n479:         \n480:     except Exception as e:\n481:         return {\n482:             \"status\": \"error\",\n483:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n484:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n485:             \"message\": f\"Failed to get status: {e}\",\n486:         }\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ### 4. Service Provider Integration\n492: \n493: #### AgentCubeProvider (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n494: \n495: The `AgentCubeProvider` provides access to the AgentRuntime CR:\n496: \n497: ```python\n498: class AgentCubeProvider:\n499:     \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n500:     \n501:     CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n502:     CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n503:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n504:     \n505:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n506:         \"\"\"Get an AgentRuntime CR by name.\n507:         \n508:         Returns:\n509:             The CR dict if found, None otherwise.\n510:         \"\"\"\n511:         try:\n512:             cr = self.custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n513:                 group=self.CR_GROUP,\n514:                 version=self.CR_VERSION,\n515:                 namespace=namespace,\n516:                 plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n517:                 name=name,\n518:             )\n519:             return cr\n520:         except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n521:             if e.status == 404:\n522:                 return None\n523:             raise\n524: ```\n525: \n526: #### KubernetesProvider (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n527: \n528: The `KubernetesProvider` provides access to standard K8s resources:\n529: \n530: ```python\n531: class KubernetesProvider:\n532:     \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service operations.\"\"\"\n533:     \n534:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n535:         \"\"\"Get status of the agent deployment.\n536:         \n537:         Returns:\n538:             Dict with status info including:\n539:             - status: \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\"\n540:             - replicas: number of replicas\n541:             - available_replicas: number of available replicas\n542:         \"\"\"\n543:         try:\n544:             deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(\n545:                 name=self._sanitize_name(agent_name),\n546:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n547:             )\n548:             \n549:             status = deployment.status\n550:             available = status.available_replicas or 0\n551:             desired = status.replicas or 0\n552:             \n553:             if available == desired and desired > 0:\n554:                 state = \"ready\"\n555:             elif available < desired:\n556:                 state = \"pending\"\n557:             else:\n558:                 state = \"error\"\n559:             \n560:             return {\n561:                 \"status\": state,\n562:                 \"replicas\": desired,\n563:                 \"available_replicas\": available,\n564:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n565:             }\n566:             \n567:         except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n568:             if e.status == 404:\n569:                 return {\"status\": \"not_found\"}\n570:             raise\n571: ```\n572: \n573: ---\n574: \n575: ## Data Models\n576: \n577: ### AgentMetadata (Relevant Fields)\n578: \n579: | Field | Type | Used In |\n580: |-------|------|---------|\n581: | `agent_name` | `str` | invoke, status |\n582: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | invoke, status (published check) |\n583: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (header) |\n584: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (endpoint) |\n585: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (endpoint fallback) |\n586: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict]` | status (provider selection) |\n587: \n588: ### Status Response Schema\n589: \n590: ```python\n591: {\n592:     \"status\": str,  # \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\", \"not_published\", \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"created_no_status\"\n593:     \"agent_name\": str,\n594:     \"agent_id\": Optional[str],\n595:     \"endpoint\": Optional[str],\n596:     \"provider\": str,  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n597:     \"message\": str,\n598:     # For k8s provider:\n599:     \"deployment\": Optional[Dict[str, Any]],\n600:     # For agentcube provider:\n601:     # Additional CR status fields\n602: }\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ---\n606: \n607: ## Error Handling\n608: \n609: ### Error Patterns\n610: \n611: All errors are handled via `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n612: \n613: ```python\n614: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n615:     console.print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", style=\"red\")\n616:     if verbose:\n617:         console.print_exception()\n618:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n619: ```\n620: \n621: ### Specific Error Cases\n622: \n623: | Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n624: |----------|------------|---------|\n625: | Invalid JSON payload | `json.JSONDecodeError` | \"Invalid JSON payload - {details}\" |\n626: | Invalid header format | `typer.Exit(1)` | \"Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\" |\n627: | Agent not published | `ValueError` | \"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\" |\n628: | Missing router_url | `ValueError` | \"router_url is required in metadata for agentcube provider\" |\n629: | No K8s deployment | `ValueError` | \"No Kubernetes deployment found...\" |\n630: | HTTP error | `httpx.HTTPStatusError` | propagated with status code |\n631: | K8s API error | `kubernetes.client.ApiException` | propagated |\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## Configuration\n636: \n637: ### Environment Variables\n638: \n639: The invoke command respects these environment variables (via metadata):\n640: \n641: | Variable | Used For |\n642: |----------|----------|\n643: | `ROUTER_URL` | Default router URL if not in metadata |\n644: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload manager for AgentCube provider |\n645: \n646: ### Metadata File Resolution\n647: \n648: The `MetadataService` loads metadata in this order:\n649: 1. `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n650: 2. `{workspace}/agent.yaml` (fallback)\n651: 3. `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n652: \n653: ---\n654: \n655: ## Testing Strategy\n656: \n657: ### Unit Tests\n658: \n659: 1. **InvokeRuntime tests**:\n660:    - Payload validation\n661:    - Header parsing\n662:    - Endpoint URL construction\n663:    - Session header injection\n664:    - Error handling\n665: \n666: 2. **StatusRuntime tests**:\n667:    - Status extraction from CR\n668:    - Status extraction from Deployment\n669:    - Not published detection\n670:    - Error state handling\n671: \n672: ### Integration Tests\n673: \n674: 1. **Invoke command E2E**:\n675:    - Invoke with JSON payload\n676:    - Invoke with custom headers\n677:    - Invoke against both providers\n678: \n679: 2. **Status command E2E**:\n680:    - Status for published agent\n681:    - Status for unpublished agent (exit code 1)\n682:    - Status for error state (exit code 1)\n683: \n684: ---\n685: \n686: ## Security Considerations\n687: \n688: 1. **Header handling**: Headers are parsed carefully to prevent injection attacks\n689: 2. **No secrets in logs**: Verbose mode does not log sensitive headers\n690: 3. **HTTPS preferred**: Endpoint URLs should use HTTPS in production\n691: 4. **K8s RBAC**: Status checks require appropriate K8s permissions\n692: \n693: ---\n694: \n695: ## Future Enhancements\n696: \n697: 1. **WebSocket support**: Real-time status updates\n698: 2. **Log streaming**: Stream agent logs during invocation\n699: 3. **Retry logic**: Automatic retry with exponential backoff\n700: 4. **Batch invoke**: Invoke multiple agents in parallel\n701: 5. **Output templating**: Custom output format templates\n702: \n703: ---\n704: \n705: ## References\n706: \n707: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n708: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n709: - [AgentCube Python SDK](../../python-sdk/design.md) - SDK design patterns\n710: - [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md) - CR API details\n\n(End of file - total 710 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands for the AgentCube project. These commands enable users to interact with deployed agents and check their deployment status.\n\n**AR:** AR-023  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              CLI Layer                                        │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775894148986,"end":1775894148996}}}}
